item.title: Want to get ahead at work? Risk the awkward moments | Henna Pryor
item.description: When we avoid feeling awkward, we often miss an opportunity for growth, says workplace performance expert Henna Pryor. She shares tips on embracing discomfort for the sake of self-betterment and shows how pushing past the "cringe chasm" — the gap between how we perceive ourselves and how others see us — can open up chances to get ahead at work and in life. After the talk, Modupe shares wisdom on how to get over the fear of being cringe. Feed: https://feeds.feedburner.com/iTunesPodcastTTBusiness
